iand(i, j) returns the bitwise logical and of integers i and j.

i = 0  j = 0  iand(i,j) = 0
i = 1  j = 1  iand(i,j) = 1
i = 2  j = 1  iand(i,j) = 0
i = 3  j = 2  iand(i,j) = 2
i = 10  j = 12  iand(i,j) = 8
i = 15  j = 5  iand(i,j) = 5

direct examples:
iand(10, 12) = 8
iand(15,  5) = 5
iand( 7,  3) = 3
iand( 8,  1) = 0
